<p>The <code>timestamp</code> function formats a full timestamp.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | timestamp{close}</pre>
<p>Current: <b>{echo {now} | timestamp}</b></p>

<h2>Custom Format</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | timestamp('Y-m-d H:i:s'){close}</pre>
<p>ISO format: <b>{echo {now} | timestamp('Y-m-d H:i:s')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | timestamp('d/m/Y H:i'){close}</pre>
<p>European: <b>{echo {now} | timestamp('d/m/Y H:i')}</b></p>

<h2>Readable Format</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | timestamp('l, F j, Y \a\t g:i A'){close}</pre>
<p>Full: <b>{echo {now} | timestamp('l, F j, Y \a\t g:i A')}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | timestamp('Y-m-d H:i') | replace(' ', 'T'){close}</pre>
<p>ISO-ish: <b>{echo {now} | timestamp('Y-m-d H:i') | replace(' ', 'T')}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Combines date and time formatting. Uses PHP date format codes.</p>
